Key Match Events: Paul van Meekeren's fiery spell proved crucial for Dutch as he took four wickets for 23 runs
Scott Edwards scored a feisty half-century to resuscitate the Dutch innings
Bas de Leede got the key dismissal of Mehidy Hasan Miraz for 35
Post-Match Reflections: Scott Edwards commented that the Dutch were awesome with the ball and probably even more so on the field
The result leaves the reigning champions England 10th and last in the standings
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dutch seamers varied their pace and extracted bounce from a slow wicket
Bangladesh allowed the Dutch lower order to accumulate 74 runs in the final 10 overs to establish a respectable total
Others: Wesley Barresi repaired the damage with a breezy 41
Colin Ackermann did not last much longer
Shoriful Islam and Mahedi Hasan cleaned up the tail
